d by a set of ingoing and outgoing amplitudes:\n\n\u03a8(x)\n\n7\u2212\u2192\n\n(Aa, Ba)\n\nwith a = 1, 2, 3 . . .\n\n(31.12)\n\nBut we should remember that not all sets of amplitudes define a stationary energy state.", "embedding": [-0.007090476, 0.0065713846, 0.052774988, -0.05204396, -0.016880628, -0.020291083, -0.013468551, -0.02125045, -0.041095104, 0.0826573, 0.05455273, 0.01995224, -0.015964119, 0.0004605622, -0.031100772, 0.04405131, -0.019596927, -0.008850647, -0.07766151, 0.016252592, 0.016580692, -0.009886526, -0.06649753, -0.036746945, -0.03920031, 0.009100056, 0.020355243, 0.017069768, 0.010666363, 0.046685446, 0.020829761, -0.041583944, 0.009643981, -0.04317499, 0.0027608369, 0.00014601092, -0.023275014, -0.044969767, 0.015630873, -0.020750675, 0.03275782, -0.0050758817, -0.0021357678, -0.021845948, -0.010076452, -0.029207552, 0.023122482, -0.002355499, -0.028101541, -0.024141356, -0.015369493, 0.0043683415, 0.028082464, -0.021562325, -0.040819746, -0.01688098, 0.012367382, 0.008194868, -0.028081467, 0.020507548, 0.04483652, -0.007864795, -0.011483676, -0.030961338, -0.0061370754, 0.024704019, -0.021879235, 0.054935794, 0.006233801, -0.050414838, -0.010998177, 0.0022507554, -0.00058862986, 0.016342545, -0.011254123, 0.017441373, 0.0146573065, -0.036531594, -0.05302161, -0.016307293, -0.0075750602, -0.014363617, -0.037970513, 0.017028496, -0.029226936, 0.014697883, -0.03244596, 0.004827614, 0.018017286, -0.0029265946, 0.0342301, 0.059375275, 0.004232402, -0.018089231, 0.029866226, 0.030810317, 0.010559792, 0.02291714, 0.028574027, 0.022042844, -0.018900013, 0.077480294, -0.022173584, 0.0284544, -0.022554638, 0.058838084, -0.008862695, 0.034687262, 0.005018142, -0.031297687, 0.040324815, -0.019515079, 0.008139287, 0.0058835405, 0.007957272, 0.01590376, 0.03088315, 0.008075198, -0.0012860735, -0.03130186, -0.016837498, -0.005814669, 0.040405706, 0.016761798, 0.00063649064, 0.016796688, -0.0030051002, 0.013569266, -0.033354525, -0.017919488, 0.0190494, -0.